Happily ever after 🏰 

#brideaesthetic #thewhitefiles #weddinginspiration #francewedding #destinationweddings 

Planning: @etvoilaweddings 
Dress: @lelitebridal 
Tux: @suitsupply 
MUAH: @jmronquilloglamteam @jm_honeyz 
Flowers: @charlotte_flowerandtwig

It was my hope that our wedding day would feel as if it was torn from the pages of a modern fairytale. Not because that is a representation of our day to day life (which is a far more simple routine of taking Weaver for walks and making grocery lists) - but because that is how our time together has always made me feel.

Planning: @etvoilaweddings 
Flowers: @charlotte_flowerandtwig 
Furniture & Decor: @jolibazaar 
Venue: @chateaurobernier 
Photographer: @martinaskrobotphotography 
Cocktail design: @nailthecocktail 

#weddinginspiration #weddingtabledecor #withjoy #romanticbride #francewedding #bridesrealweddings

THE dress 🥹
I wore an ever-so-slightly blush colored “Maeve” dress (yes, you read that correctly!) by @moniquelhuillierbride from @lelitebridal.
During my first try-on appointment, the stylist at @lelitebridal mentioned that they had a dress called “Maeve” and asked if I would want to try it. I was on a mission to try on as many dresses as possible, so I said yes without even seeing it.
When I put it on, I loved it. The subtle blush tone, the silhouette, the floral lace appliqués, the dramatic train… it was beautiful. But I had gravitated towards off-the-shoulder necklines, which this dress did not originally have. I asked if it would be possible to add an off-the-shoulder sleeve, and with a few pins and pieces of tulle, the dress was absolutely perfect for me (the 3rd photo was taken on that day!).

I have admired @moniquelhuillierbride’s gowns for years, so getting married in a blush colored dress from the designer - bearing my name - truly felt like fate.

Bedroom of my dreams now that we’ve upgraded to a king mattress! These are the 3 keys to our parisian-inspired bedroom: 
1. The focal point: A big, luxurious place to rest your head (think 5-star-hotel-bed vibes). Our new @saatva mattress (we went with their latex hybrid) is truly like sleeping on a cloud and has transformed our space (ad) ☁️ 
2. Architectural details: we added decorative mouldings and a chandelier to give the room a distinctive French feel 
3. Provincial-style furniture and antique details: look for vintage (or vintage inspired) pieces with delicate curved edges and scroll or floral motif carvings/embellishments. I also look for intricate gold details, like the pulls on my dresser or pretty little picture frames ✨
